<section class="card">
  <h2>Short Season Notes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Start indoors—direct sowing often finishes too late in short seasons.</li>
    <li>Transplant while it’s still cool. Heat and drought slow heading.</li>
    <li>Protect young transplants from wind and cold snaps for a smoother start.</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section class="card">
  <h2>Variety Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Early/mid-season varieties are usually more reliable than long-storage types.</li>
    <li>Days-to-maturity varies a lot—choose based on your frost window.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
